Cookie - is an entry of two strings (key-value), which is stored on clients browser and is sent to server each request.
* It also allows to store some data on client side for further identification
* Server adds new cookies in clients browser or changes ones that are already exist
! Whenever client makes request - server get its cookies

Cookie structure:
1) Entry of name-value
2) Expiration date
3) Domain, Path (which domain refers, on request to which address should be sent)